        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/2–2745</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Acting Secretary of
                        State</hi>
                    <note n="21" xml:id="d732fn21">This conversation was reported to Moscow in
                        telegram 467, March 2, 1945, 4 p.m., not printed.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-27">February 27,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Soviet Ambassador called on me this afternoon and, in continuation of the
                    talk which I had last week with the Soviet Chargé d’Affaires, brought up the
                    possibility of the inclusion in the Fourth Protocol of a provision for the
                    application of $300,000,000 for industrial equipment prior to July 1, 1945, but
                    the equipment to be made available to Soviet Russia after July 1, 1945.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph</hi> C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
